<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>If you are new here, not well known, or not liked by the popular people then anything you say here will (especially if a loved player disagrees) be forever used against you - here, in game, and in real life if anyone happends to have your real life information.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->The length of time that your posts will remembered is up to the memory of the person with whom you have been arguing (and the memory of the spectators.)  If you're new or relatively unknown, I'd believe that you have less of a chance of having your posts remembered.  Long after her departure, the name of Seamyst still invokes a reaction from those who were here during her time, because she was a long-time regular.<br>
<br>
For someone who hardly posts here to be remembered by the masses, he'd have to post something incredibly noteworthy.  Sure, I remember Pinolian's crazy flame-out, because it was ridulously over-the-top.  If he had come here and started posting about nonsense like driving granite-filled dump trucks, though, I'd have forgotten his name.<br>
<br>
As for information being used against you in real life, I'm not sure why you'd offer real life information to people on the boards; nor do I understand what real-life consequences you would face.  I can't think of the last time that Novbre stole the newspaper from my front steps or Nandarie left an empty milk carton in my fridge.<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>If you fight back against flames made by Saryrn celebrities or on their behalf against you eventually you will no longer be permitted to play the game on this server. You will end up guildless and group-less. (can you hear the measured tread of the goose-stepping jackbooted Saryrn celebrities and thier followers?).<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Damn it, I missed the last convention of the Illuminati.  Can someone please forward me the latest revision of our collection of blacklisted names?  I have to make sure that I don't group with someone who was excommunicated by the Council of Elders for daring to cross the great ones on this, the holiest of grounds.  I fear the consequences if I was found grouping with someone whose permission to play had been revoked.<br>
<br>
